data.enText: the hard part of the foot of some animals, for example horses
meat that is sold, transported, etc. on the hoof is sold, etc. while the cow or sheep is still alive
if you do sth on the hoof , you do it quickly and without giving it your full attention because you are doing sth else at the same time
to kick a ball very hard or a long way
to go somewhere on foot; to walk somewhere

data.chText: 我们一路步行走到了第42街。
data.enText: We hoofed it all the way to 42nd Street.

ex.chText: 走了很长时间之后，他双脚酸痛。
ex.enText: His feet hurt after the long walk.
Keep away from the horse's hind feet.

synonyms.bx: 多指人的脚，也可指动物的蹄。

ex.enText: The claws of a tiger are very sharp.

synonyms.bx: 指鸟、兽、昆虫等锋利而弯曲的爪尖。

ex.chText: 老师问他的学生们一头牛有几只蹄子。
ex.enText: The teacher asked his pupils how many hooves a cow has.

ex.chText: 他不知道该如何画狮爪。
ex.enText: He doesn't know how to paint a lion's paw.

ex.chText: 把你的脏爪子从我身上拿开！
ex.enText: Keep your dirty paws off me!

synonyms.bx: 指动物包括爪尖在内的爪子，比较软；也可喻指人的手，作此义解时常含贬义。

the horny covering of the end of the foot in ungulate mammals

example: let's hoof it to the disco

value.def: The hooves of an animal such as a horse are the hard lower parts of its feet.

example.ex: The horses' hooves often could not get a proper grip.
